---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const email = 'info@imaginaryinteriors.com';
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Imaginary Interiors" description="How Imaginary Interiors handles your data.">
  <div class="wrap">
    <section class="hero" style="grid-template-columns:1fr;padding-bottom:10px">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow">Legal</div>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="prose">
        <p class="updated">Last updated: July 4, 2026</p>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how Imaginary Interiors ("we", "us") collects, uses and
          protects information when you use imaginaryinteriors.com. We keep the site lightweight and
          only use information that helps us operate the website, understand what is useful and
          improve the experience.</p>

        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We may collect basic usage information such as pages visited, referrer, device type,
          browser type and approximate region through analytics tools. If you save styles or rooms,
          those selections are stored locally in your browser on your device. We do not require an
          account to browse the site.</p>

        <p>
          If you contact us by email, we receive the information you choose to send, such as your
          name, email address and message content.</p>

        <h2>How we use information</h2>
        <p>
          We use information to operate and maintain the website, understand which pages and ideas
          are most helpful, improve site content and design, respond to messages and protect the
          site from misuse.</p>

        <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Imaginary Interiors uses Vercel Web Analytics to understand site traffic and performance.
          Saved styles and rooms are stored in your browser's local storage so they can appear when
          you return on the same device. You can clear this saved data at any time through your
          browser settings.</p>

        <h2>Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          Our pages may link to third-party websites, retailers and affiliate partners. Those sites
          are operated independently and have their own privacy policies. We are not responsible for
          the privacy practices or content of third-party websites.</p>

        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can use your browser settings to block or clear cookies, local storage and other
          website data. If you email us, you can ask us to delete or stop using the personal
          information you provided, subject to any information we need to keep for legitimate
          business, security or legal reasons.</p>

        <h2>Data security</h2>
        <p>
          We take reasonable steps to protect information, but no website or internet transmission
          can be guaranteed to be completely secure. Please avoid sending sensitive personal
          information through email.</p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
          "Last updated" date above.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about this policy? Email <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
